I agree. It shouldn't be a general PvP forum. It should be a Rogue PvP forum. A place where where rogues on the PvP servers can easily find PvP tactics and information on aquiring things or completing quests on a PvP server. <br>
<br>
Like the Burning Rapier for example. When buying the Sparkling Sapphire on a PvP server, it's best (imo) to get the money from Rivervale and do it at night (in game). You're less likely to run into trouble this way. Too many people are afraid to cross Kithicor at night and even in the day it's not as crowded as East Commonlands.<br>
<br>
Other such things include getting Blood Spirits as a Dark Elf rogue and obtaining the Mask of Deception on a Teams PvP server.<br>
