<br>
We can use the other forums. We could also delete the Safehouse and use the EQ forums instead, and sort through all the non-rogue posts. "Just" different tactics? "Totally" is a much more correct term. I don't want to add my good info to you're irrelevant info. Adding a cup of clean water to a cup of dirt never cleaned the dirt, and one's man's treasure is another man's trash. Without searching, post the forum - not even a link, just the forum -  Bluud's guide is in. I sure as heck have no idea where it is, even after requesting it be put in the Library. Oh, you want to read some good PvP stuff? Well don't search around for a guide, look in the new forum.<br>
<br>
Think about the Safehouse as a bunch of marbles lying on a tile floor. You have your news marbles over here, so you put them in the news bag. You have your rants over here so you put them in the rants bag. You have your ooc marbles over here so you put them in the ooc bag. Finally you have nearly everything organized, with just a small pile of marbles of varying colors. Well I keep losing my PvP marbles!<br>
<br>
To restate what Verant has said, EQ will always be primarily PvE. The red servers are PvE with PvP added, not the other way around. I fully understand this, and so does any other pvp rogue with his head screwed on good. But it certainly gets frustrating to scrounge around for the info I need that could be lurking in nearly any forum.<br>
<br>
And hey, if this bombs out, delete it. It's happened before, anyone remember the AC Portal?<br>
